  additionalData: '{"LanguageCode":"en-us","Items":[{"contentID":-1,"properties":{"state":null,"modifiedBy":null,"modified":null,"pullDate":null,"releaseDate":null,"versionID":null,"referenceName":"developerarticles","definitionName":"DocArticle","itemOrder":1},"fields":{"title":"Developing with Agility","metaTitle":"How To Start Developing With Agility","slug":"developing-with-agility-cms","description":"Unlimited creative freedom on any platform or framework.","content":"{\\u0022blocks\\u0022:[{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022OJrEJrO_kB\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022raw\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022html\\u0022:\\u0022\\u003Cdiv style=\\\\\\u0022padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\\\\\\u0022\\u003E\\u003Ciframe src=\\\\\\u0022https://player.vimeo.com/video/1055987658?h=37841213d4\\u0026amp;badge=0\\u0026amp;autopause=0\\u0026amp;player_id=0\\u0026amp;app_id=58479\\\\\\u0022 frameborder=\\\\\\u00220\\\\\\u0022 allow=\\\\\\u0022autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write; encrypted-media\\\\\\u0022 style=\\\\\\u0022position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\\\\\\u0022 title=\\\\\\u0022Guided Walkthrough - Developer Settings\\\\\\u0022\\u003E\\u003C/iframe\\u003E\\u003C/div\\u003E\\u003Cscript src=\\\\\\u0022https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\\\\\\u0022\\u003E\\u003C/script\\u003E\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022uTSXyF6sSu\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Agility is built to be flexible and powerful so you can design a solution that suits your needs.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022Uk0mBL9kQP\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Being a Headless CMS, there are infinite ways to integrate with Agility. Agility handles storing your content, providing a UI to manage it, and APIs to access it.\\u0026nbsp;\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022TUXjDY1uf_\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022quote\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022You develop and deploy your website (or app, IoT device, etc.) outside of Agility and pull-in content using our platform SDKs or REST API.\\u0026nbsp;\\u0022,\\u0022caption\\u0022:\\u0022\\u0022,\\u0022alignment\\u0022:\\u0022left\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022TrXPNuHSUC\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022You can build and deploy your digital solution in any framework, on any platform. Your content and where it is displayed is entirely decoupled.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022Ky129R0xHr\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022image\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022file\\u0022:{\\u0022url\\u0022:\\u0022https://cdn.aglty.io/agility-cms-docs/images/block-editor/Developing With Agility-09232024183348.png\\u0022,\\u0022size\\u0022:{\\u0022height\\u0022:600,\\u0022width\\u0022:940,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022png\\u0022}},\\u0022caption\\u0022:\\u0022\\u0022,\\u0022withBorder\\u0022:false,\\u0022stretched\\u0022:false,\\u0022withBackground\\u0022:false}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u002284nK8wjUPF\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022header\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Content Architecture\\u0022,\\u0022level\\u0022:2}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u00229xiCg0zAIz\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022In order to retrieve Agility content via the API, you must have content set up in your instance that you can query. We call this process of setting up your content and layouts \\u003Cb\\u003EContent Architecture\\u003C/b\\u003E.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022evYFRNfLeC\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Think of this as defining what fields your editors will need for each type of content.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022aOWtXzF4-t\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022This includes:\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022c5sunSFd7F\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022list\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022style\\u0022:\\u0022unordered\\u0022,\\u0022items\\u0022:[{\\u0022content\\u0022:\\u0022\\u003Cb\\u003ESetting up Content Models\\u003C/b\\u003E - Content Models represent the structure for a type of content. You can then initialize lists of content based off a model that you can query with the API.\\u0022,\\u0022items\\u0022:[]},{\\u0022content\\u0022:\\u0022\\u003Cb\\u003ESetting up Component Models \\u003C/b\\u003E- These are the components that editors can add to pages so they can control what content (and order) will display on a page.  Component Models are similar to Content Models in that they are comprised of fields, but they can only be added to pages. \\u0022,\\u0022items\\u0022:[]}]}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022XeP6LGObzz\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022quote\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Component Models typically correspond to frontend components in a website that will render HTML templates with the content from the CMS.\\u0022,\\u0022caption\\u0022:\\u0022\\u0022,\\u0022alignment\\u0022:\\u0022left\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022rnyADEb-56\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022header\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Accessing Content\\u0022,\\u0022level\\u0022:2}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022AoEZktdF4j\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Once you have content set up and some layouts with some components on them, you are ready to start retrieving content from the CMS to integrate into your solution.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022LZpt5qDHCZ\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Agility builds and maintains a variety of different ways to access content including framework specific SDKs to make it even easier to get your content.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022EbYP2NY_gR\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022list\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022style\\u0022:\\u0022unordered\\u0022,\\u0022items\\u0022:[{\\u0022content\\u0022:\\u0022Using a Framework/Starter\\u0022,\\u0022items\\u0022:[]},{\\u0022content\\u0022:\\u0022Using an SDK\\u0022,\\u0022items\\u0022:[]},{\\u0022content\\u0022:\\u0022Using the REST API with any programming language\\u0022,\\u0022items\\u0022:[]}]}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022omPtZXVVtD\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022header\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Deploying your Solution\\u0022,\\u0022level\\u0022:2}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u00222vho0mkNtV\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Agility is always hosted and maintained by Agility, but you can build a deploy your digital solution anywhere.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022U8bB5mFmpa\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Agility has some built in hosting integrations with \\u003Cb\\u003EVercel \\u003C/b\\u003Eand \\u003Cb\\u003ENetlify\\u003C/b\\u003E\\u0026nbsp;that can make it even easier to deploy your website and set up a content preview.\\u0022}}]}","section":{"contentid":10,"fulllist":false},"section_TextField":"Introduction","section_ValueField":"10","concept":{"contentid":47,"fulllist":false},"concept_TextField":"Overview","concept_ValueField":"47"},"seo":{"metaDescription":"Agility CMS is built to be flexible and powerful so you can design a solution that suits your needs. Start developing now!","metaKeywords":null,"metaHTML":null,"menuVisible":null,"sitemapVisible":null},"scripts":{"top":null,"bottom":null}},{"contentID":-1,"properties":{"state":null,"modifiedBy":null,"modified":null,"pullDate":null,"releaseDate":null,"versionID":null,"referenceName":"developerarticles","definitionName":"DocArticle","itemOrder":2},"fields":{"title":"Page Management in a Headless CMS","metaTitle":"Using PageManagement in a Headless CMS- Agility","slug":"page-management-in-a-headless-cms","description":"How pages empower editors and promote happy, productive developers.","content":"{\\u0022blocks\\u0022:[{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022OcSPN_5zNK\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022While Agility is a Headless CMS and can boast all the benefits that come with that, there is one area where we take a different approach than others. Page Management.\\u003Cbr\\u003E\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022tlRW02MxhM\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Yep, we are opinionated about it and\\u0026nbsp;stand by it!\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022nj2oxXrqCr\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022One of the main concepts of a Headless CMS is that the CMS should make no assumptions about how Developers will use it.\\u0026nbsp; This means as an architect you often start with a blank slate and you configure your content architecture exactly to your specifications. \\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022nYmM6YEx8K\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022That\\u0027s great, and something we provide out-of-the-box with\\u0026nbsp;Content Models, but there are some limitations to this approach when using a Headless CMS to build websites and it affects both Developers AND Editors.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022y9jFyJEHMy\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Let\\u0027s take a closer look.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u00226F2hWfN4m9\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022header\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Using Content Models to Manage Page Content\\u0022,\\u0022level\\u0022:2}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022VC3YNnW3_m\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Let\\u0027s go through some content architecture that\\u0027s using Content Models for each type of page and see how it holds up. For simplicity, let\\u0027s start with a single landing page for an upcoming video game.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022B-0B_PZHsk\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022\\u003Cb\\u003EPage:\\u003C/b\\u003E\\u0026nbsp;Home\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022pJv1UV1qBC\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022image\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022file\\u0022:{\\u0022url\\u0022:\\u0022https://cdn.aglty.io/agility-cms-docs/images/block-editor/Screenshot 2024-'... 700015 more characters,
