le":{"contentid":599,"fulllist":false},"article_TextField":"How the Angular Blog Starter Works","article_ValueField":"599"},"seo":{"metaDescription":null,"metaKeywords":null,"metaHTML":null,"menuVisible":null,"sitemapVisible":null},"scripts":{"top":null,"bottom":null}},{"contentID":-1,"properties":{"state":null,"modifiedBy":null,"modified":null,"pullDate":null,"releaseDate":null,"versionID":null,"referenceName":"angular_articlelisting_liste4b4dee","definitionName":"ListedArticle","itemOrder":1},"fields":{"article":{"contentid":600,"fulllist":false},"article_TextField":"Deploying Angular to Vercel","article_ValueField":"600"},"seo":{"metaDescription":null,"metaKeywords":null,"metaHTML":null,"menuVisible":null,"sitemapVisible":null},"scripts":{"top":null,"bottom":null}},{"contentID":-1,"properties":{"state":null,"modifiedBy":null,"modified":null,"pullDate":null,"releaseDate":null,"versionID":null,"referenceName":"angular_rightorleftalignedlid2af85","definitionName":"ListedLink","itemOrder":1},"fields":{"explicitURL":{"href":"https://angular.io/guide/component-overview","target":"","text":"Angular Components Overview"},"description":"Learn how components are the main building blocks for Angular applications.","explicitIcon":"ExternalLinkIcon"},"seo":{"metaDescription":null,"metaKeywords":null,"metaHTML":null,"menuVisible":null,"sitemapVisible":null},"scripts":{"top":null,"bottom":null}},{"contentID":-1,"properties":{"state":null,"modifiedBy":null,"modified":null,"pullDate":null,"releaseDate":null,"versionID":null,"referenceName":"overviewarticles","definitionName":"DocArticle","itemOrder":10},"fields":{"title":"CMS Environments, Development, and Content Workflow Best Practices","metaTitle":"Best Practices - CMS Environments, Development, and Content Workflow","slug":"cms-environments-development-and-content-workflow-best-practices","content":"{\\u0022blocks\\u0022:[{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022LqVQ9419fC\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Agility CMS is designed to be flexible, easy-to-use, and empower you to do more, faster!\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u00226RPbubdhuy\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Agility is a headless CMS, thus your content is decoupled from your presentation layer (i.e. your website). Separating your content from your code allows for greater flexibility of how you use that content, it also allows you to maintain separate workflows for changes to content and code.\\u0026nbsp;\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022oZdF_4y75Y\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022This guide will walk you through how you can design content and code workflows that will make it faster than ever to publish content changes, while also maintaining a high level of quality control over it and the code presenting that content.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u00222kf2NWpRto\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022header\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Instance Environments\\u0022,\\u0022level\\u0022:2}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022gVGAbmTDiu\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Agility is a multi-tenant CMS, hosted and managed in the cloud, by us.\\u0026nbsp;\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022kD_XzYwxm0\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Agility\\u0027s flexible content models and page management means you can use Agility to power one or\\u0026nbsp;many different websites\\u0026nbsp;or apps. In most cases, you will have a single production Agility CMS instance (environment) and its content will be consumed by a website.\\u0026nbsp;\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022HJ3yIic1uI\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022While the Agility CMS instance and our APIs are managed by Agility, the website(s) are managed by you.\\u0026nbsp;\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022I3YCfpfgC3\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022With your production CMS environment, all content can be previewed prior to publishing. When you Preview your content from the CMS, Agility will open a new tab in your browser and initiate a preview session using your configured preview website.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022pI_MxS8-6B\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022header\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Additional Instance Environments\\u0022,\\u0022level\\u0022:2}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022uC2NB2LGss\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Additional instance environments represent replicas of your production instance, designed for developers\\u0026nbsp;to test changes to their content architecture\\u0026nbsp;before implementing a change in your production instance environment. This re-enforces the separation of concerns between code and content by allowing developers to validate and test their code with a variety of test content separate from the production content.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022jqW2Mk79P6\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Developers should have access to additional instance environments to test changes, while editors who need to manage content should only have access to the production instance environment.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022k3q8aDyr38\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022Whether you need additional instance environments or not will depend on how large your team is and what level of risk you are comfortable with.\\u0022}},{\\u0022id\\u0022:\\u0022EX8uDHIhsR\\u0022,\\u0022type\\u0022:\\u0022paragraph\\u0022,\\u0022data\\u0022:{\\u0022text\\u0022:\\u0022It\\u0027s important to note that additional instance environments are not designed to be used by editors or as part of a typical content workflow. We recommend keeping all content workflow within your production instance, utilizing the built-in workflows for'... 403096 more characters,
